medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms started when the patient was 14 years and 9 months old, presenting with eunuchoid habitus, no pubertal development (pubic hair and genitalia Tanner stage 1), and height remaining around normal until the onset of hypogonadotropic hypogonadism. He was treated with testosterone enanthate starting from age 15 years and 4 months, and by 17 years and 7 months demonstrated some secondary sexual development.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Hypogonadotropic hypogonadism, anosmia, dental agenesis (agenesis of eight teeth). Previous treatment included testosterone enanthate.
medical_history.family_history: The mother presented with olfactory dysfunction, dental agenesis (agenesis of six teeth), but had normal stature and fertility, with no abnormalities in other family members.
